From Ron Albury Subject Re Procomm Plus for windows You have a lot more problems keeping up with hardware interrupts in Windows than in DOS regardless of what communication software you are Try the following Turn off disk write cache for the disk you are downloading The cache will save up so much that when it grabs control of the machine it takes too long to write to disk and you loose Use a different UART for your serial The old UART's or can only buffer one character The new UART's can buffer which should be plenty for most You can run windows to find out what UART is on the Ron